Today, I've been tested the deck API (and hopefully the card API) I made previously. However, I've came across a couple errors: where the first one was:

Found deck:⟨07aca71f-96a4-4d3a-9f60-af4cf1a25158⟩ for the id field, but a specific record has been specified

This error was happening as the id specified in the $whatwas different from $data which took some time to investigate. The second was:

Api(FromValue { value: Object(Object({"cards": Array(Array([])), "creator": Thing(Thing { tb: "user", id: String("testusername") }), "id": Thing(Thing { tb: "deck", id: String("1073d113-ff11-4911-90cf-f4dbd9153617") }), "name": Strand(Strand("test")), "read_access": Array(Array([])), "write_access": Array(Array([]))})), error: "missing field `tags`" })

I have not solved this error yet, but trying to debug by logging what the application is trying to run on the database, it's attempting to add the following to the database:

DeckDatabase { id: Thing { tb: "deck", id: String("1073d113-ff11-4911-90cf-f4dbd9153617") }, creator: Thing { tb: "user", id: String("testusername") }, name: "test", cards: [], tags: [], share_link: None, read_access: [], write_access: [] }

So, I'm currently scratching my head as tags is defined. This is likely an error on my end, but it could be an issue with the database I'm using. Since, I'm not able to view the exact SQL the database tried to run, I made a pull request to hopefully help me fix issues quicker in the future.

After investigating some more, I realised I did not define the tags column and after I did, the problem was fixed.

Now, it's time to test the rest of the endpoints.

GET /v1/deck/{id}
...

This endpoint was initially not working, but it was because I did not register it. Once I did, everything was successful.

PATCH /v1/deck/{id}
...

This worked as expected too.

DELETE /v1/deck/{id}
...

Finally, deleting also works. However, any linked flashcards will now have an invalid reference. Perhaps a method needs to be added to update them.

  • Adding method to update all linked cards
  • Make the GET return a better response when getting an non-existent card.
